Bright spark whom I did cradle in life's prime,
Thy laughter was the music that could buoy
This weary heart beyond the hands of time.

I held thee close, a promise in thine eyes,
A future drawn in innocence and grace;
Now silence sits where once thy sweet voice lies,
And shadows fill the hollows of thy place.

Thy hand, so small, once clasped my trembling own,
A pledge of love no death may now unbind.
Though thou art gone, thou'rt never quite unknown—
Thy light persists within the depths of mind.

So sleep, my joy, in stillness soft and deep,
While I, earthbound, shall weep—and love—thee."
